<div class="card">
  <div class="card__body">
    <h2>Purpose</h2>
    <p>HelloDeploy provides a free deployment platform for personal and educational projects. This policy describes what you may and may not deploy. Using HelloDeploy means you accept these rules.</p>

    <h2>Permitted Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Personal web applications and APIs for learning or portfolio purposes.</li>
      <li>Open-source project demos and educational coursework.</li>
      <li>Internal tools used by you and your project team members.</li>
      <li>Any application whose content and behaviour are lawful in your jurisdiction.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Prohibited Use</h2>
    <p>The following are not allowed on HelloDeploy under any circumstances:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Illegal content.</strong> Anything that violates applicable law, including copyright infringement, child exploitation material, or content that incites violence.</li>
      <li><strong>Malware and exploits.</strong> Applications designed to attack, infect, or compromise other systems or users.</li>
      <li><strong>Phishing and fraud.</strong> Impersonating other services, collecting credentials under false pretences, or conducting scams.</li>
      <li><strong>Cryptocurrency mining.</strong> Using platform resources to mine or generate cryptocurrency.</li>
      <li><strong>Abusive traffic generation.</strong> Running bots, scrapers, spam mailers, or load-testing tools that target systems you do not own.</li>
      <li><strong>Network scanning.</strong> Probing, scanning, or attacking other hosts from within a deployed container.</li>
      <li><strong>Circumventing resource limits.</strong> Attempting to exceed your quota through technical means, account duplication, or other workarounds.</li>
      <li><strong>Reselling access.</strong> Offering HelloDeploy capacity to third parties as a commercial service.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Resource Responsibility</h2>
    <p>Your application must operate within the limits described in the <a href="/service-limits">Service Limits</a> page. Applications that consistently exceed CPU or memory limits may be suspended without notice to protect other users.</p>

    <h2>Account Rules</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>One account per person. Creating multiple accounts to circumvent limits is prohibited.</li>
      <li>You are responsible for all activity under your account, including actions taken by project team members you invite.</li>
      <li>Do not share your account credentials.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Enforcement</h2>
    <p>Violations are handled progressively:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Warning</strong> — notification by email for a first or minor violation.</li>
      <li><strong>Suspension</strong> — account access suspended while the violation is reviewed.</li>
      <li><strong>Termination</strong> — account and all associated data permanently removed for serious or repeat violations.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>Severe violations (malware, illegal content, active attacks) may result in immediate termination without a prior warning.</p>

    <h2>Reporting</h2>
    <p>If you believe another user is violating this policy, contact the platform administrator at <strong>hensonsagorsor@gmail.com</strong>.</p>
  </div>
</div>
